<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFFD6820459A374DB8A5FD24" pageId="8" pageNumber="291" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFFD6820459A374DB8A5FD24" blockId="8.[151,1437,510,1330]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFD6820459A374DBB39FDED" bold="true" box="[199,322,582,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFFD68204482374CB978FDEC" authority="Cartwright &amp; Dostine, 2022" authorityName="Cartwright &amp; Dostine" authorityYear="2022" box="[479,771,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bamboosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFD68204482374CB978FDEC" box="[479,771,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Polyplectropus bamboosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFD68204651374CB913FDEC" bold="true" box="[780,872,583,609]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2194045FFFD68204651374CB913FDEC" box="[780,872,583,609]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
appears most similar to the male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFFD6820404D374CBB30FD08" authority="Kumanski 1979" authorityName="Kumanski" authorityYear="1979" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chapmani">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFD6820404D374CBFE7FDEC" box="[1296,1436,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">P. chapmani</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFFD682045CA3760BB30FD08" author="Kumanski, K." box="[151,331,619,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291" pagination="193 - 219" refId="ref15026" refString="Kumanski, K. (1979) Trichoptera (Insecta) from New Guinea. Aquatic Insects, 1 (4), 193 - 219. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 01650427909360996" type="journal article" year="1979">Kumanski 1979</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from New 
<collectingCountry id="F34961BCFFFD6820448C3760B859FD08" box="[465,546,619,645]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Guinea</collectingCountry>
but differs in that the inferior appendages in ventral view appear more nearly truncate posteriorly with an acute apicomesal angle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFFD6820459A37B9BBE4FB48" pageId="8" pageNumber="291" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFFD6820459A37B9B897FCD0" blockId="8.[151,1437,510,1330]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFD6820459A37B9BBD9FD40" bold="true" box="[199,418,690,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Description, male.</emphasis>
Spur formula: 3:4:4. Wings (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFFD682047AE37B8B93FFD40" box="[755,836,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1624,1648]" captionTargetBox="[329,1258,324,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-75@9.[318,1269,309,1601]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Polyplectropus spp. n. 13–15. Polyplectropus bamboosa sp. nov.: 13, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 14–15, male genitalia: 14, left lateral; 15, ventral. 16–17. Polyplectropus berryensis sp. nov.: 16–17, male genitalia: 16, left lateral; 17, ventral.Abbreviations: F1 = fork 1; F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); int. app. = intermediate appendage (paired); st. IX = sternite IX." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559747/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFFD6820417237B8BEBAFD40" authority="Cartwright &amp; Dostine, 2022" authorityName="Cartwright &amp; Dostine" authorityYear="2022" box="[1071,1217,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="berryensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFD6820417237B8BEBAFD40" box="[1071,1217,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">P. berryensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFD6820419437B8BF5FFD40" bold="true" box="[1225,1316,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2194045FFFD6820419437B8BF5FFD40" box="[1225,1316,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Length of each forewing 
<quantity id="4CA68CC9FFFD6820446037DCBBEDFD7C" box="[317,406,727,753]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="291" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
. Head, body, and wings light brown. Wing venation: each forewing with forks 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5 present; fork 1 short, fork 2 sessile with its length about 1.6 times length of fork 3; fork 3 with short footstalk, fork 4 slightly shorter than fork 3, fork 5 about 1.6 times length of fork 4. Hind wings each with forks 2 and 5 present; fork 2 sessile, fork 5 about 1.2 times length of fork 2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFFD6820459A366CBB04FB2C" blockId="8.[151,1437,510,1330]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFD6820459A366CBB73FC0C" box="[199,264,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Male.</emphasis>
Posterior margin of sternum IX with slight angular extension near mid-height in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFFD68204067366CBFF4FC0C" box="[1338,1423,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1624,1648]" captionTargetBox="[329,1258,324,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-75@9.[318,1269,309,1601]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Polyplectropus spp. n. 13–15. Polyplectropus bamboosa sp. nov.: 13, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 14–15, male genitalia: 14, left lateral; 15, ventral. 16–17. Polyplectropus berryensis sp. nov.: 16–17, male genitalia: 16, left lateral; 17, ventral.Abbreviations: F1 = fork 1; F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); int. app. = intermediate appendage (paired); st. IX = sternite IX." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559747/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Fused terga IX+X membranous (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFFD682047583680B8FDFC28" box="[517,646,906,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1624,1648]" captionTargetBox="[329,1258,324,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-75@9.[318,1269,309,1601]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Polyplectropus spp. n. 13–15. Polyplectropus bamboosa sp. nov.: 13, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 14–15, male genitalia: 14, left lateral; 15, ventral. 16–17. Polyplectropus berryensis sp. nov.: 16–17, male genitalia: 16, left lateral; 17, ventral.Abbreviations: F1 = fork 1; F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); int. app. = intermediate appendage (paired); st. IX = sternite IX." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559747/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Figs 14, 15</figureCitation>
). Intermediate appendages laterally compressed, in lateral view irregularly subovate, approximately 1.8 times as long as maximum width, broadest near middle, tapered slightly in posterior 1/3, with rounded apex (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFFD682044B336D8B83BFC60" box="[494,576,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1624,1648]" captionTargetBox="[329,1258,324,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-75@9.[318,1269,309,1601]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Polyplectropus spp. n. 13–15. Polyplectropus bamboosa sp. nov.: 13, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 14–15, male genitalia: 14, left lateral; 15, ventral. 16–17. Polyplectropus berryensis sp. nov.: 16–17, male genitalia: 16, left lateral; 17, ventral.Abbreviations: F1 = fork 1; F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); int. app. = intermediate appendage (paired); st. IX = sternite IX." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559747/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
, int. app.), in ventral view apices appearing acute (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFFD6820412036D8BEAAFC60" box="[1149,1233,978,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1624,1648]" captionTargetBox="[329,1258,324,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-75@9.[318,1269,309,1601]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Polyplectropus spp. n. 13–15. Polyplectropus bamboosa sp. nov.: 13, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 14–15, male genitalia: 14, left lateral; 15, ventral. 16–17. Polyplectropus berryensis sp. nov.: 16–17, male genitalia: 16, left lateral; 17, ventral.Abbreviations: F1 = fork 1; F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); int. app. = intermediate appendage (paired); st. IX = sternite IX." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559747/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages robust, dorso-ventrally depressed but curved and flanged basolaterally (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFFD682046AA36FCBE02FB9C" box="[1015,1145,1014,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1624,1648]" captionTargetBox="[329,1258,324,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-75@9.[318,1269,309,1601]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Polyplectropus spp. n. 13–15. Polyplectropus bamboosa sp. nov.: 13, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 14–15, male genitalia: 14, left lateral; 15, ventral. 16–17. Polyplectropus berryensis sp. nov.: 16–17, male genitalia: 16, left lateral; 17, ventral.Abbreviations: F1 = fork 1; F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); int. app. = intermediate appendage (paired); st. IX = sternite IX." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559747/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Figs 14, 15</figureCitation>
, inf. app.); in lateral view appearing irregularly rectangular, broadest near middle, tapered slightly posteriorly, with distal ends shorter than distal ends of intermediate appendages (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFFD682047013134B8CBFBD4" box="[604,688,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1624,1648]" captionTargetBox="[329,1258,324,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-75@9.[318,1269,309,1601]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Polyplectropus spp. n. 13–15. Polyplectropus bamboosa sp. nov.: 13, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 14–15, male genitalia: 14, left lateral; 15, ventral. 16–17. Polyplectropus berryensis sp. nov.: 16–17, male genitalia: 16, left lateral; 17, ventral.Abbreviations: F1 = fork 1; F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); int. app. = intermediate appendage (paired); st. IX = sternite IX." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559747/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
); in ventral view, each appendage semi-circular, rounded laterally, narrowly separated in distal third, exised in basal half mesally (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFFD682046363168B9BBFBF0" box="[875,960,1122,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1624,1648]" captionTargetBox="[329,1258,324,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-75@9.[318,1269,309,1601]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Polyplectropus spp. n. 13–15. Polyplectropus bamboosa sp. nov.: 13, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 14–15, male genitalia: 14, left lateral; 15, ventral. 16–17. Polyplectropus berryensis sp. nov.: 16–17, male genitalia: 16, left lateral; 17, ventral.Abbreviations: F1 = fork 1; F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); int. app. = intermediate appendage (paired); st. IX = sternite IX." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559747/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Phallus tubelike, with slightly expanded phallobase (
<figureCitation id="13653DA9FFFD68204443318CBB09FB2C" box="[286,370,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1624,1648]" captionTargetBox="[329,1258,324,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-75@9.[318,1269,309,1601]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Polyplectropus spp. n. 13–15. Polyplectropus bamboosa sp. nov.: 13, apices of right fore- and hind wings, dorsal. 14–15, male genitalia: 14, left lateral; 15, ventral. 16–17. Polyplectropus berryensis sp. nov.: 16–17, male genitalia: 16, left lateral; 17, ventral.Abbreviations: F1 = fork 1; F2 = fork 2; F3 = fork 3; F4 = fork 4; F5 = fork 5; inf. app. = inferior appendage (paired); int. app. = intermediate appendage (paired); st. IX = sternite IX." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559747/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFFD6820459A31A0BBE4FB48" blockId="8.[151,1437,510,1330]" box="[199,415,1195,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFD6820459A31A0BB58FB48" box="[199,291,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFFD6820459A31C4B98AFB67" box="[199,1009,1231,1258]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFFD6820459A31C4B98AFB67" blockId="8.[151,1437,510,1330]" box="[199,1009,1231,1258]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFD6820459A31C4BB35FB64" bold="true" box="[199,334,1231,1257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Etymology.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFD6820440831C4BBB0FB64" box="[341,459,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Bamboosa</emphasis>
—named after the 
<typeStatus id="54E59F8EFFFD682047C131C4B8B7FB64" box="[668,716,1231,1257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">type</typeStatus>
locality (Bamboo Creek).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFFD6820459A31F8BE73FABF" pageId="8" pageNumber="291" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFFD6820459A31F8BE73FABF" blockId="8.[151,1437,510,1330]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFD6820459A31F8BB40FA80" bold="true" box="[199,315,1267,1293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Remarks.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus id="54E59F8EFFFD682044F031F8B874FA80" box="[429,527,1267,1293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">holotype</typeStatus>
male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFFD6820472931F8B9ECFA80" authorityName="Cartwright &amp; Dostine" authorityYear="2022" box="[628,919,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Polyplectropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bamboosa">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFD6820472931F8B9ECFA80" box="[628,919,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="291">Polyplectropus bamboosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known. It has been collected from the type locality in the Litchfield N.P. area of the Top End of the NT (latitude 
<geoCoordinate id="EE6A47EBFFFD682046C3301CB987FABF" box="[926,1020,1303,1330]" degrees="13.06" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="8" pageNumber="291" precision="555" value="-13.06">13.06°S</geoCoordinate>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
